bio.experienceSummary:
Based in Portland, Oregon

A little bit about myself,

I like working with kids because kids are fun and bring new light and new perspective. Children remind us to laugh, love but also enjoy the small parts of life.

Throughout high school, I babysat a set a triplets, bilingual students and also children with special needs! Helping them with their schoolwork, and basic life tasks. Two of my favorite activities to do with kids are crafts and baking!

Additionally, I have my own transportation I'm a non-smoker, I am CPR certified, bilingual, and obtain a College degree in both biology and Spanish from Spelman College!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! My name is Mitra, and I have a deep passion for caring for and nurturing children. With years of experience working with kids through tutoring, mentorship, and volunteer programs, I understand the importance of patience, engagement, and creating a fun yet structured environment for children to thrive in.

As a responsible and dependable babysitter, I prioritize safety, creativity, and emotional support, ensuring that each child feels comfortable and cared for. My experience ranges from helping with homework and educational activities to organizing engaging playtime and bedtime routines. I also enjoy encouraging curiosity through interactive learning and play!

As a college student, I appreciate a flexible schedule while still being fully committed to providing the best care. Whether it's a one-time babysitting need or a long-term arrangement, I look forward to building a strong and trusting relationship with both the child and the family.

Hello loving parents 
My name is Taryn
I am an experienced, engaging, responsible, high profile nanny / house manager
I have 12 yrs experience, professionally working with children of all ages and various family dynamics. I've previously worked as a floral designer and event planner and this comes to my advantage when being organized in a household, creative while playing, planning activities, play dates and even birthday parties. 

About me:
~CPR/first aid certified
~Can care for children of all ages 
~Plan/host play dates, birthday parties 
~Help with household errands, book appointments
~Meal prep
~Driving
~Personal assistance 
~Organization 
~Date Night and Overnight care
~Pet care
~Traveling Domestically/Internationally and many more 

The list is short but the experience will speak for itself:) 
Please feel free to reach out. I would love to have the chance to talk and see if we are a good fit for each other

Talk soon

description.displayText:
As a mother of two young boys, I've been through many different babysitters and nannies. Taryn is hands down one of the best!  She has a true passion for children which shines through everything she does.  From her warm spirit, incredible patience, to non-stop energic play and creativity, Taryn makes caretaking look so easy.  

I met Taryn when both of my boys were in diapers.  Taryn managed everything from feeding, potty training, bathing, to play and entertainment and would also do extra duties such as dishes and laundry.  Most of all, Taryn created incredible memories while caring for my boys that they still talk about her to this day with huge smiles from ear to ear.  To know that my boys are in loving and protected hands is everything a mom dreams of! Taryn is forever our favorite nanny!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello!

I am CPR/First Aid certified and am able to get dropped off at work. I have 6 years childcare experience and 2 years nannying experience.

I have always loved children and began working in the daycare at my church and babysitting infants-elementary since I was 15 years old. 
Additionally, I have babysat for family/family friends from when they were newborn-3 years old.
For the past two years, I have been a professional nanny, caring for children between the ages of 5 weeks old and 11 years. 

My motto in life is "live, love, laugh," and I believe children sense that from me, which is why we get along so well. I hope you will feel the same way when we start working together. I'm excited to hear from you!

description.originalText: Wante was wonderful! My 4 year old loved her and had a great time and she was so good with my 1 year old. We came to Atlanta for a wedding and Wante babysat my kids for two evenings. Even though it was our first time meeting her, I (and my kids) were so comfortable with her and everything went great. bio.experienceSummary: I recently graduated and currently work full time during the week. I tutor in most subjects on the weekends and also babysit occasionally too! Please feel free to reach out

Hi there! I'm Covid/Flu vaccinated and got my Tdap booster. 
I have raised 4 great children of my own, (and rescue dogs and cat) and have been proactive in every stage of their development. 'Momming' is what I do best. I'm a native English speaker, but can have a basic baby conversation in several languages! I sing and do funny voices: Babies give me 2 thumbs up! 
Tidying up and baby laundry are done while the baby is sleeping. I have my own dependable car, impeccable driving record, and infant-child CPR-First aid certification. I also love when there are pets at work! 
If you're searching for a caregiver you can trust implicitly with your precious newborn, then please contact me. I have great references from my previous employers (4 doctors+), and currently focusing on newborns through 1 year. 
Please be in touch!

description.originalText: Pamela was great with your baby girl. As a first time mom I felt extremely comfortable leaving her with Pamela when I went back to work. She also offered us lots of great advice as well. I am thankful for our time with her!

bio.experienceSummary: I've been caring for children for the past three years, and I'm passionate about helping them learn, grow, and develop. I believe that every child deserves a chance to thrive, and I'm committed to providing a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment for them. I'm patient, calm, and creative, and I love playing games and coming up with fun activities that will keep the children engaged and entertained. I'm also very comfortable enforcing household rules and routines. I have a college degree, CPR Training, and Early Child Development Coursework. I'm confident that I have the skills and experience to provide excellent care for your children.

description.originalText: Tacari has been a great addition to our family! She is great with our 20 month old and takes initiative on different tasks around the house! I would highly recommend her!

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! Welcome to my profile. I have a passion for kids because they bring me joy! I consider myself a great sitter/nanny because I give attention the small details of keeping children happy and occupied through engaging activities that encourage social and personality growth! For many years, I have enjoyed caring for children of all ages. My experience ranges from interning at daycare centers, family sitting, nanny families, church nursery work, early childhood classes, and more! I'm fun, responsible, loving, reliable, trustworthy, and very excited to work with you and your little one(s)! Please feel free to ask any questions you may have!

description.originalText:
Gloria has been an absolute blessing for our family. Despite our son being very colicky and clingy, she remained calm, collected, and incredibly patient throughout. Her nurturing demeanor and confidence gave us the peace of mind we needed to leave our baby at home while we went to work. She kept us updated with photos and messages throughout the day, which truly eased our worries and allowed us to focus on our jobs.

Even with a commute of 30-40 minutes, she has always been responsible, punctual, and dependable. Her dedication and care have been invaluable to us, and we are so grateful for everything she does!

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm Aleshia and I was born in Austin Texas. I moved to Dallas Georgia where I attended high school and played travel volleyball. Now, I currently stay in Buckhead Georgia and major in business management.

I was an infant teacher at the Goddard School until I discovered Nannying and fell in love. I simply love children and enjoy helping them learn & grow at every stage of their lives. My strengths as a nanny are that I am very responsible, reliable, and a caring person! I have cared for children as young as 6 weeks up to 8 years of age. I enjoy encouraging kids to be creative with activities such as painting, coloring, reading and exploring outside. I think it's important for children to try different activities and expand their horizons, and I love being apart of that! 
Being a nanny has given me the opportunity to meet not only the kids but their families and their surroundings. Every kid I take care of is a new child experience I acquire, I look forward to meeting your family!!

description.originalText: I was looking for a nanny to watch my 5 year old twins once a week for 2 months. My twins loved her! She sat down and did school work with them, made lunch and made it a mission to get some fresh air each time she came. She is punctual, kind, reliable, and has a true passion for kids! I would definitely hire again!

bio.experienceSummary:
I have 4 years of experience as a Household Assistant/Estate Manager and as a Personal Assistant. I am also an experienced babysitter/nanny with 20+ years experience. 

I have taken the "Big Little Feelings" course and am drawn to Montessori, gentle/respectful caretaking. I am proactive, loving, patient, kind, communicative, organized and resourceful. I play guitar, sing and like hanging out with my dog. I have studied some psychology and some child development. I have an (SUV) and a clean driving record. :) I am fully vaccinated and boosted against COVID and the flu.
